text:
As the U.S. passed a grim milestone of 200,000 coronavirus-related deaths, Vice President Mike Pence sent his condolences to victims and their families while also saying things could have been worse
https://t.co/uMyLyKyD9z

name: politico
text:
House Speaker Nancy Pelosi and Treasury Secretary Steven Mnuchin have cemented a deal on a short-term spending fix that would avert a government shutdown next week, with the House expected to pass the measure tonight
https://t.co/53v2SIMmv0

name: politico
text: The House voted to extend federal funding through mid-December and punt the threat of a government shutdown until after the presidential election https://t.co/jkqMMs4ZMR

name: politico
text:
A new poll from The Des Moines Register and Mediacom Iowa shows both Trump and Biden receiving support from 47 percent of likely voters surveyed just six weeks from Election Day
https://t.co/Xo21J8yDV2
